</FONT>
<HR size="1" color="#12350C">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">
Rather than crap i3ullseyes threads with these comments, I will mention them here.  There have been a few common changes people keep mentioning that I would like to comment on before we all jump on the bandwagon.<P><B>1. Giving our Mez extra range to compensate for lack of Insta-Mez.</B> Not a bad idea, but I think this would be a better compensation for lack of armor/speed/healing, rather than a lack of insta.  Insta will still win over range, because you will very rarely have an opportinity to use your maximum range.  Plus, many are saying "bolt range would be nice, but 1700 would be just fine." NO NO NO.  An incoming bard/healer will be hammering on the insta key & targetting the nearest person.  When that nearest person is hit, it will be at full 1500 range plus they will have their 350 radius, thus hitting us with an instant at up to 1850 range...thats why bolts are 1875 range.  Plus the fact that we can only "estimate" our range since we can't cast on the run. If this is going to truly be our "solution" then it had better be 2300, but I would still much prefer an instant over range.  I dont want to hide WAY in the back ALL the time.<P><B>2. Pets: Remove the "Charming Debuff" & "Give us Pet Buffs"</B> First off, I personally think they should get rid of the "debuff."  It's really lame, and I would much rather have a summoned pet than a debuffed charmed one.  At the same time, the claims that pets are debuffed to a blue or even green are somewhat exagerated.  Based on my testing, I would say a level 50 Telamon is lowered to perhaps a 47-48.  This is still noticable, but hardly a blue con. (I can notice a difference between a 49 & a 50).  However, here's the thing, I also run around with my Enhance cleric in tow & always fully buff my pet.  Now, most won't have the luxury of buffs that high, but I can tell you that my level 50 Tela, fully buffed, stands Toe-to-Toe with a RED Greater Telamon without ANY assistance from me.  So high cleric buffs take it from about 48 up to 55 or so!?!?!  With my cleric in tow, I am not soloing, I am actually duoing (even though I play both), so the relative power is not all that unreasonable.  However if every sorcerer were to have a TRUE 50 pet, plus self-buffs, that would potentially give a 55+ pet which truly would be overpowered (Did I actually say that?).  Plus with self buffs, we would not be able to take cleric buffs, and thats what clerics are for.  If we can get a "True 50," I think that is enough for the pet, and any energy spent toward a "pet buff line" could be spent elsewhere & avoid the future calls of being "overpowered."  We could still potentially have an "overpowered" pet, but it would require a high enhance cleric, and that is their only job...to make everyone else overpowered.  My enhance cleric can BARELY kill a blue on her own...a yellow is suicide, but she does her job well.  <IMG SRC="smile.gif" border="0"><BR>A better pet "buff" would be allowing us to send them from bolt range, as has been mentioned a couple times.  These allows us to use our pets more, but keep our of harms way ourselves...which is the point of having a pet anyway.<P><B>I became a Sorcerer because I wanted to be a "Support" player.</B> This is not the case for everyone.  I want to be able to help my group/guildmates, but I also love to solo.  Not everyone wants to be forced into a "support" role.  I most certainly do not.  Our strength is our versatility.  We may be the best solo class in the game for PvE, why must we be forced to always group in RvR?  As long as Mind Line changes are scaled so that any "additions" or "boosts" are viable to characters specced to 30ish in Mind, it will not force anyone to be a full-time support player.  If we are forced to go to 40-44 in order to get an Insta or Bolt Range Mez or AE Cure Mez or whatever, then we are forced into a full-time support role because we wont have the offensive capabilities to do anything else.  While we are not supposed to be the "primary damage dealers," we ARE supposed to have some serious offense...otherwise we would have chain & HPs for defense.  I dont want to be stuck with no defense AND no offense.  Let's be cautious about what we ask for.<P>--------------------<P><B>Quote 7/2/02 - i3ullseye, Sorcerer Team Lead: Actually no, i am not 'your' representative. this has been stated before. many TLs do not post ANYWHERE except the pendragn boards. Noone has to try to get ANY feedback from the general populace.</B><P><B>**********************</B><P>Palomides / Alat-Seldi<BR>Mezmo - Level 50.1 Sorcerer<BR>Tagalong - Level 43 Enhance Cleric<BR>Siege - Level 33 Armsman<BR>Terrenus - Level 28 Earth Wizard<BR>Miracle - Level 11 Rejuv Cleric<BR>Recurve - Level 10 Scout
</FONT>
