<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">
I'm with you on this increased pet range.  as nice as a true-50 pet would be, I never had problems with my pet being too weak.  What sort of loser sends in a pet than sits down?  We have like 9 gazillion sexy debuffs to be tossing out.  Str/Con, Dex/Quick, Dex, and Str debuffs, my pet could take on even-cons only losing about 1/3-1/4 his health. orange cons were around 2/3-1/2.  not bad, if you ask me.  the problem is that not everyone debuffs their enemies 4 times as the power consumption on that is about 1/4 of your total power, and it takes a good 5 seconds in between AoE debuffs, which means a lot of ouchies if they're resisted.<P>As for range, 2300 is too much.  I think it's too much now, thank goddess for it only being on neasight and amnesia.  For this line, I'm rooting for a passive ability.  Spellturn is dumb, since usually I get 3 instas on me within 5 seconds, so turning one of them away would be a horrible waste of my time.  Instead I'd rather have a passive sorc-only line.  It was always my impression that if you spec in a line you should be resistant to its damage type.  Cold wizards shouldn't be bothered too much by cold damage... hate to break it to you.  Mind sorces shouldn't be bothered too much by mezzes.  That's why I wanted a solid 30, 40, and 50 passive ability or maybe a 25, 35, 45 passive or something.  This would be dorky in PvE, since you rarely get mezzed there.  but in rvr, it would increase your chance to resist a mezz spell completely to 15, 30, and 50% accordingly.  This means that when someone casts an insta on me, at level 50 I would have a 50% chance of resisting it were I to be specced in mind.  Keep in mind this is a complete no-effect resist where "you resist the spell" not a mez-duration shortened by 50% thing, as I think those are dorky unless you get them really high, like 60+% high.<P>anywho, as for being a 100% support role, I think I agree a little bit... but if we got some skills in 44+ mind I would be ok speccing 100% mind.  we have pets for offense, decent debuffs...  even with 50 in one line the 40+ half-dings give you around 20 or so spec in another line.  with 13 from items and whatnot that's at the 2/3 level mark for decent variance with the base-body-nukes or base-body DoT.  Good enough for me considering I should be a mez-queen and I'm not.<P>Oh well, let's see what we get. if we get.
</FONT>
