<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">
Exactly stellaris. I believe pets were meant to protect the caster (ie taking aggro off you, and dealing dmg so mobs remain aggro on the pet)<P>The issue becomes usefulness in RvR. They often have trouble hitting a PC and do little actual dmg as a "fire and forget" spell unless you happend to find a solo mage (yeah that happens often) and do nothing to protect you.<P>This is the very reason I advocate that pets actually intercept attacks for the pet owner when close by. Thats the only way they can provide any kind of real defense for us. Also, to make pets viable they need to allow us to charm orange cons that are debuffed or remove the debuff. Adding buffs to the mind line I don't think is the answer.<P>Adding pet range is nice too, but of all the problems, this one isnt a priority to me.<P>If someone goes full mind, they have weaker dmg and a debuffed orange con, or non-debuffed yellow can be the source of damage for the mind spec Sorc.<P>As far as being able to solo and group in RvR, etc. all I can say is that's the way it is in and RvR game. Some classes are designed to be better at soloing than others. Some were desgined to be support. That won't change. The writing is on the wall so to speak in terms of class solo vs group viability. IS is "fair" or "good"? Maybe not, but that's how DAoC works and I don't suspect it will change all that much.<P>Also, the whole grouping thing for RvR has a lot more to do with the numbers game. You are welcome to solo, but you will likely just get zerged anyway, so why would you if your are not a stealther? The only real soloers are stealthers because of that stealth ability. So for eveyone to be able to solo in RvR, it would require everyone having stealth. Point: Grouping is "forced" on non-stealthers" only because it's a matter of players taking the safety in numbers appraoch(you want more people to match their people, they want/get more to match your number, effectively eliminating the possibility of soloing since you just get run over), not class specific issues. <P>As far as being a Support player, well, Sorc's don't have to be as they can go Body spec. and not be as much of a support type player, whereas Mind is a more support type spec (given that it was a workable line). The choice is the player's.
</FONT>
